The ANC in the Western Cape is shocked after the burning down Swartland district hospital in Malmesbury on Saturday night.ANC spokesperson Maurencia Gillion called on the provincial government to immediately start an investigation into the cause of the fire and maintenance problems experienced at this critical institution serving mostly poor people.&#8220;We are also concerned about the possible destruction of valuable documents and records of patients,&#8221; said Gillion.She added: &#8220;We also call for calm as patients are moved to other hospitals in the province.&#8221;The cause of the fire is still unknown. There are no reports of injuries.TNA Reporter 